RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS POLO BAR vied in the two path early, shook loose inside when ready on the turn, edged off and remained well clear while ridden out. STOLEN ART unseated her rider and ran off about half mile during the post parade, was in tight at the far turn, moved wide and continued gamely while no threat to the winner. THIS DAMSEL MAYFLY pressed the winner briefly inside, saved ground throughout and finished willingly. RUSSIAN TOTHE WIRE broke very awkwardly, rushed wide to challenge the winner on the turn then flattened out in the stretch. MISSY PIGGY steadied repeatedly in the opening quarter mile then moved wide and had no response. SPIN THE MOON dropped back early, steadied into the far turn and gave way readily.

ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back early, steadied into the far turn and gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAPITURE'S LADY chased the loose pacesetter, further behind into stretch then surged through the final furlong and quickly pulled clear. SHY SHY controlled the pace in hand, widened into the stretch then was unable to hold off the winner. JOCASTA prompted the pace two and three wide then was finished after half a mile. REAL AWESOME broke alertly then dropped back, was outrun and trailed losing contact with her field.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 5F Turf CR: 86. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MANHATTAN CHERRY eased back between early duelers before quarter mile, swung very wide into the stretch, rallied with the runnerup and won the head bob. CRIMINAL RECORD saved ground, angled out and moved with winner in the stretch and just missed. A ROZE AND WINE engaged in a heated duel inside, cut the corner leading into the stretch, finished gamely but could not hold off the top pair. ESSENTIAL BELLA broke sluggishly, raced inside and finished well while no threat. BIRDIE BE GONE raced three wide off the dueling leaders and faltered. DREAMING BIZ lagged far behind and was never in contention. NOEL'S ANGEL vied outside in a blistering duel to the stretch and faded.
